        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1967-06-10T16:05:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1967-06-10T16:05:00-05:00" n="258"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d258">
                <head>258. Memorandum From the President’s Special Assistant (<persName
                        corresp="#p_RWW1" type="from">Rostow</persName>) to President <persName
                        corresp="#p_JLB1" type="to">Johnson</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d258fn1">Source: <persName corresp="#p_JLB1"
                            >Johnson</persName> Library, National Security File, Country File,
                        Middle East Crisis, <gloss target="#t_CIA1">CIA</gloss> Intelligence
                        Memoranda. Top Secret; Trine.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1967-06-10T17:05:00-04:00">June 10, 1967, 5:05 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">Mr. President:</p>
                <p>These intercepts<note n="2" xml:id="d258fn2">Attached is a preliminary version of
                        the material discussed in <ref target="#d284">Document 284</ref>. Other
                        copies of this material in preliminary and later versions are in the
                        National Security Agency, Center for Cryptologic History, Historical
                        Collection, Series VIII, Crisis Files, Box 16; Naval Security Group Records,
                        NSG Box 896, <gloss target="#t_USS1">USS</gloss>
                        <hi rend="italic">Liberty</hi>, Pre 76, Box 1, <gloss target="#t_USS1"
                            >USS</gloss>
                        <hi rend="italic">Liberty</hi>, 5750/4, Chronological Message File; and
                        Central Intelligence Agency, DDO/<gloss target="#t_NE1">NE</gloss> Files,
                        Job 68–S–626, Box 1, Folder 5, Israeli Air Including Attack on <hi
                            rend="italic">Liberty</hi>, and ibid., Folder 8, <gloss target="#t_USS1"
                            >USS</gloss>
                        <hi rend="italic">Liberty</hi> and Other Naval Activity.</note>—showing some
                    honest ambiguity about the ship after the attack—suggest that there may have
                    been a breakdown of communications on the Israeli side; that is, the tactical
                    base which first received word that the ship was American may not have flashed
                    that information to other air force and naval units.</p>
                <p>We shall, of course, analyze this affair further.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RWW1">Walt</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
